================================================================================
  HOW THE RESULTS WERE CALCULATED
================================================================================

Ground truth logic:
  Causal query   -> 'Does X cause Y?'  -> correct answer = Yes
                    (X is the real causal feature from your data)
  Spurious query -> 'Does Z cause Y?'  -> correct answer = No
                    (Z is validated as spurious by step2b)

A model is FOOLED when it answers 'Yes' to a spurious query.

Metric formulas:
  Causal accuracy   = correct Yes answers / total causal queries   x 100
  Spurious accuracy = correct No  answers / total spurious queries x 100
  Overall accuracy  = (correct Yes + correct No) / all queries     x 100

